#### Installing Termux ####
Go to F-Droid website
Search for Termux
Download only APK
Install App by using APK, you may need to give Permissions
Open App
type: yes | pkg upgrade
yes | pkg install git

#### Installing Andronix ####
Search for Andronix in Google Play Store
Open App
On Adnroid 12+ You need to fix some process_killing issues that are internal in android. Follow the guides given by the Android docs.
Click on Linux Distribution
Click on Ubuntu
Click on Ubuntu 20.04
Click on CLI Only
Paste script in Termux
Press Enter #This process will take a long time and you may need to give permissions

#### Giving Access to Internal Storage ####
Exit out of distro by typing:
exit
Give Termux storage access by typing:
termux-setup-storage
Change start file of distro:
nano start-ubuntu20.sh
Uncomment "#command+=" -b /data/data/com.termux/files/home:/root"
ctrl+X
y
enter

#### Clone Repo ####
Go to directory where you want to clone repo with bash. 'storage/shared/' is where the internal storage is
git clone https://github.com/AnnaMatuszynska/biotool-photosynthesis.git

#### Install ComPhot ####
./start-ubuntu20.sh
apt update -y && apt upgrade -y
apt install software-properties-common curl -y
add-apt-repository ppa:deadsnakes/ppa
apt install python3.10 -y
curl -sS https://bootstrap.pypa.io/get-pip.py | python3.10
Go to directory with ComPhot repo with bash controls:
cd /
cd sdcard #For internal phone storage
cd Documents
cd biotool-photosynthesis
pip install -r requirements.txt

#### Run Streamlit ####
streamlit run Start.py
